        desc:'Granada is a compact, passionate city where one of the world\'s greatest palaces — the Alhambra — watches over flamenco cave bars and a university that produces more students per capita than almost anywhere else in Spain. It\'s the cheapest major city on this list, the free-tapas-with-every-drink culture is real and generous, and the Sierra Nevada ski resort is just 45 minutes away.',
        highlights:['Alhambra Palace & Generalife — UNESCO World Heritage, must-book in advance','Albaicín district — Moorish hilltop neighbourhood (UNESCO listed)','Free tapas bars — every drink comes with a free tapa. Always.','Sierra Nevada — Spain\'s top ski resort, 45 minutes by bus','Sacromonte caves — authentic flamenco in hillside cave venues'],
        studentLife:'The University of Granada has 55,000 students in a city of 232,000 — that\'s a 1:4 student-to-resident ratio, giving Granada the most student-dense atmosphere in Spain. Life is affordable, social, and centred around the city\'s plazas and tapas bars. Spanish language immersion is natural and total.',
