        desc:'Bilbao is Europe\'s greatest urban regeneration story. Once an industrial, grey port city, today it\'s a world-class cultural destination — the Guggenheim effect transformed it entirely. Expect serious rain (bring a good jacket), exceptional food (pintxos are a way of life), and a fierce, proud Basque identity that makes this one of Spain\'s most unique cities for students who want something different.',
        highlights:['Guggenheim Museum Bilbao — Frank Gehry\'s titanium masterpiece','Casco Viejo (Siete Calles) — the vibrant old town with pintxos bars','Mercado de la Ribera — Europe\'s largest covered food market','San Mamés Stadium — Athletic Club\'s iconic cathedral of football','Nervión Riverfront — the regenerated waterfront walkway'],
        studentLife:'The University of the Basque Country (EHU/UPV) is a major research university with bilingual Basque-Spanish instruction. The university has a strong international exchange programme. Bilbao\'s compact size (everything is walkable) and low crime rate make it ideal for students.',
